# üéô Python Voice Assistant AI

A voice-controlled AI assistant built using Python that can recognize speech commands and perform tasks like opening websites and playing music.

---

##  Features

-  Wake word detection ("Joy")
-  Open websites (Google, YouTube, LinkedIn, GitHub)
-  Play songs from a predefined music list
-  Text-to-Speech response system
-  Speech Recognition using Google API

---

## üõ† Technologies Used

- Python
- SpeechRecognition
- Pyttsx3 (Text-to-Speech Engine)
- PyAudio
- Webbrowser Module

 

### Installation & Setup

1. Clone the repository ```bash
git clone https://github.com/yuvraj-singh-027/python-voice-assistant-ai.git
cd python-voice-assistant-ai

2. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run the project
python main.py



## How It Works

The assistant continuously listens for the wake word "Jarvis".
Once activated, it listens for the next command.
The command is processed and executed.



